What is Normalization? Explain the concept

Explain about different joins available in SQL with its Syntax


Normalization is a way of organizing data in a database so that:
Data is not repeated
Data is clean and consistent
Tables are well structured
  
  Avoid duplicate data
Save storage space
Make data easy to update
Reduce errors

  INNER JOIN
  SELECT columns
FROM table1
INNER JOIN table2
ON table1.id = table2.id;

  . LEFT JOIN
  SELECT columns
FROM table1
LEFT JOIN table2
ON table1.id = table2.id;

  RIGHT JOIN
  SELECT columns
FROM table1
RIGHT JOIN table2
ON table1.id = table2.id;

FULL JOIN
  SELECT columns
FROM table1
FULL OUTER JOIN table2
ON table1.id = table2.id;

CROSS JOIN
  SELECT columns
FROM table1
CROSS JOIN table2;
